# Fight Page (Blind Model Comparison)

The fight page (`/fight`) has two states toggled by JS. Served via `app.main.fight` -> `fight.html`.

**Theme tokens live in** `app/static/css/app.css` and are documented in `../ui.mdc`. All fight colors use existing CSS custom properties only.

## State A: Landing

Centered hero with prompt input. No model dropdown ‚Äî models are selected server-side.

- **Container:** `#fight-landing.hero-container` ‚Äî centered column, `max-width: 600px`.
- **Title:** `<h1 class="app-name">Model <kbd>Fight</kbd> .</h1>`
- **Input Area:** `.input-area` > `.input-row`
  - `textarea#fight-input` ‚Äî reuses `.hero-container textarea` styles (`min-height: 100px`, `border-radius: 12px`, no resize).
  - `button#fight-send.send-btn` ‚Äî 40px circle, arrow SVG (same as chat send button).
  - `<small>` helper: "Press Enter to send ‚Äî two random models will compete".
- **Send trigger:** Enter key (Shift+Enter for newline) or click send button.

## State B: Fight Arena

Side-by-side split view. Shown after submission via JS class toggle.

- **Transition:** JS hides `#fight-landing`, removes `hidden` from `#fight-arena`, adds `.fight-active` to `<main>`.
- **`main.fight-active`** overrides: `justify-content: flex-start; padding: 0`.
- **Container:** `#fight-arena.fight-container` ‚Äî flex column, full height, `padding: 1rem`, `gap: 0.75rem`.

### Fight Header (`.fight-header`)

- Shows the submitted prompt text. Card-style bar with ellipsis overflow.
- `.fight-prompt-label` ‚Äî muted "Prompt:" prefix.
- `#fight-prompt-text` ‚Äî base color, populated by JS.

### Split Panes (`.fight-panes`)

- CSS grid: `grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr`, `gap: 0.75rem`, `flex: 1`, `min-height: 0`.
- Stacks vertically at `@media (max-width: 640px)`.

Each pane (`.fight-pane`):
- **`.pane-label`** ‚Äî uppercase header ("MODEL A" / "MODEL B"), muted color, bottom border. After vote, replaced with real model name.
- **`.pane-output`** ‚Äî `flex: 1`, `overflow-y: auto`, `pre-wrap`, scrollable streamed text area. After streaming completes, `renderMarkdown(outputEl)` parses with `marked.parse()` and sets `innerHTML` + `.md-rendered` class (switches to normal whitespace with styled code blocks, lists, etc.).
- **`.pane-vote`** ‚Äî vote button at bottom, `disabled` until both streams complete.

### Post-Vote States

- `.fight-pane.winner` ‚Äî `border-color: var(--pico-primary-background)`.
- `.fight-pane.loser` ‚Äî `opacity: 0.55`.
- Winner button text changes to "Winner".
- Labels reveal real model names from vote API response.

## Backend API

- **`POST /api/fight`** ‚Äî accepts `{prompt}`. Server picks 2 random models via `random.sample(list_models(), 2)`, creates 2 jobs via `job_manager.create_job()`, saves fight to SQLite. Returns `{fight_id, jobs: [{job_id, label: "A"}, {job_id, label: "B"}]}`. Returns 400 if fewer than 2 models available.
- **`GET /sse/chat/{job_id}`** ‚Äî reuses existing SSE endpoint for streaming (events: `token`, `done`, `error`).
- **`POST /api/fight/{fight_id}/vote`** ‚Äî accepts `{winner: "A"|"B"}`. Records vote in SQLite. Returns `{model_a, model_b}` (real model names for reveal).

## Data Persistence

- SQLite table `fights` in `DB_PATH` (`data/tinybench.db`), initialised at app startup via `fight_store.init_db()`.
- Schema: `fight_id TEXT PK`, `model_a TEXT`, `model_b TEXT`, `prompt TEXT`, `winner TEXT` (nullable), `created_at TEXT`.

## JS Flow (`fight.js`)

1. On submit (Enter or click): `POST /api/fight` with prompt.
2. Transition to arena view, populate prompt header.
3. Open 2 `EventSource` connections to `/sse/chat/{job_id}` (one per pane).
4. Buffer + flush tokens at 50ms intervals (same pattern as `chat.js`).
5. Track completion via `doneCount`; enable vote buttons when both streams finish.
6. On vote click: `POST /api/fight/{fight_id}/vote`, reveal model names, apply winner/loser classes.

## Concurrency

The `GGUFRunner` has a single-model cache, so on Pi hardware the two jobs serialize naturally: model A generates first, then model B loads and generates. Both SSE streams work; one fills before the other.

